    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-18T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-18T09:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/3–1847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-18T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >March 18, 1947—5 [p.m.?]</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 18—12:28 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>860. <hi rend="smallcaps">Kosmos</hi> 1.<note n="51" xml:id="d411fn1">From the
                        Secretary of State in Moscow.</note> Your 532 of 4 p.m., 15 March refers. In
                    view of exchange of letters between Molotov and myself, I suggest the last
                    paragraph of your proposed memorandum to Soviet Government, which starts “the
                    Soviet Government in its note”, and ends “detachment of marines at Tsingtao” be
                    deleted. In its place I suggest a statement substantially as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“With regard to the matter of US troops in China, this will be <pb
                                facs="0513" n="503" xml:id="pg_503"/> covered in the exchange of
                            information referred to in the communication of the Secretary of State
                            dated 15 March.”<note n="52" xml:id="d411fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_614">p.
                                614</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I will advise Embassy here when you indicate clearance.</p>
                <p>New subject: I have discussed and given a copy of the last paragraph of your 509
                    of 8 p.m., 13 March<note n="53" xml:id="d411fn3">Not printed.</note> with Mr.
                        Bevin.<note n="54" xml:id="d411fn4">Ernest Bevin, British Secretary of State
                        for Foreign Affairs.</note> He is taking the matter up by cable with
                    London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
